# {{.Name}}

A self-contained IR evaluation track (TREC convention).

## Layout

```
{{.Name}}/
  spec.yaml          # engines + jobs + defaults
  suite.yaml         # query templates + queries
  trec/
    pool.yaml                       # generated by `bench pool`
    annotations.<strategy>.yaml     # one per judge strategy
    qrels.<strategy>.tsv            # optional TREC export
  reports/
    <run_id>.json                   # one per `bench run`
    latest.json                     # pointer to the most recent
```

## Workflow

```bash
# 1. Sanity check before burning real engine time.
bench validate {{.Name}}

# 2. Generate the candidate pool from every engine.
bench pool {{.Name}}

# 3. Grade. Pick a strategy:
#    lexical     — fast deterministic baseline
#    claude-api  — Anthropic Messages API in batches (set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
#    claude-cli  — `claude -p` per batch (no API key needed)
#    manual      — write -1 placeholders for hand grading
bench judge {{.Name}} --strategy claude-api

# 4. Run the benchmark.
bench run {{.Name}}                              # uses spec.defaults.judgments
bench run {{.Name}} --judgments claude-api       # explicit override
bench run {{.Name}} --judgments lexical          # compare against the baseline

# 5. (Optional) Export TREC qrels.
bench qrels {{.Name}} --strategy claude-api
```

## Inspecting state

```bash
bench show spec {{.Name}}
bench show pool {{.Name}}
bench show judgments {{.Name}} --strategy claude-api
```

## Resumable judging

`bench judge ... --resume` skips docs already graded in the output file.
Atomic writes mean Ctrl-C is safe — re-run with `--resume` to continue where
you left off.
